<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="65.[189,1398,724,786]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Following 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Rayah" box="[316,505,724,750]" firstAuthor="El-Rayah" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" refId="ref259989" refString="El-Rayah M. A. 1980. Systematics of African molossid bats of the subgenus Xiphonycteris of the genus Tadarida (Molossidae: Chiroptera). PhD Thesis, University of Toronto. Available from https: // idl-bnc-idrc. dspacedirect. org / handle / 10625 / 5743? show = full [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="url" year="1980">El-Rayah (1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Rayah" box="[516,578,724,750]" firstAuthor="El-Rayah" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref260050" refString="El-Rayah M. A. 1981. A new species of bat of the genus Tadarida (family Molossidae) from West Africa. Life Science Occasional Papers, Royal Ontario Museum 36: 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[598,853,724,751]" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="312 - 567" refId="ref273235" refString="Simmons N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. In: Wilson D. E. &amp; Reeder D. M. (eds) Mammal Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference: 312 - 567. The John Hopkins University Press, Baltimore." type="book chapter" year="2005">Simmons (2005: 442)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[908,1170,724,751]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="501 - 502" refId="ref263482" refString="Happold M. 2013 q. Tadarida brachyptera Short-winged Free-tailed Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 501 - 502. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="q">Happold (2013q: 501)</bibRefCitation>
, we consider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1328,1398,724,750]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leonis">
<emphasis box="[1328,1398,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[421,576,760,786]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Dysopes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachypterus">
<emphasis box="[421,576,760,786]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">brachypterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="65.[189,1399,825,1240]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[189,483,825,852]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[297,357,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 66
</bibRefCitation>
, map 102) report 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[698,858,825,852]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leonis" subGenus="Mops">
<emphasis box="[698,858,825,852]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">T. (M.) leonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from six localities, of which we were unable to trace the underlying BMNH specimens for the three southernmost records (Sud-Kivu Province). The three other localities are in the northeastern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[906,966,896,922]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">DRC</collectingCountry>
(Nord-Kivu, Haut-Uélé and Tshopo Provinces). The species was further reported from the northwestern part of the country (Yalosemba, Mongala Province and Tandala, Sud-Ubangi Province), but also from the southwestern part (Thysville [= Mbanza-Ngungu], Kongo Central Province and Léopoldville [= Kinshasa]). These last four localities were not plotted on the distribution map presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[831,1098,1037,1064]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="501 - 502" refId="ref263482" refString="Happold M. 2013 q. Tadarida brachyptera Short-winged Free-tailed Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 501 - 502. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="q">Happold (2013q: 502)</bibRefCitation>
. On her map, she painted four areas where this species occurs: northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[783,843,1072,1098]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">DRC</collectingCountry>
(with two individual localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1342,1072,1099]" name="Uganda" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Uganda</collectingCountry>
), the east African coast (from 
<collectingCountry box="[490,583,1107,1133]" name="Kenya" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Malindi</collectingCountry>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[626,703,1108,1134]" name="Kenya" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Kenya</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[745,986,1107,1134]" name="Mozambique Island" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Mozambique Island</collectingCountry>
), coastal West Africa (from 
<collectingCountry name="Sierra Leone" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
to western 
<collectingCountry box="[400,463,1143,1169]" name="Togo" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Togo</collectingCountry>
, and from western 
<collectingCountry box="[689,777,1143,1169]" name="Nigeria" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[816,1033,1143,1170]" name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Equatorial Guinea</collectingCountry>
) expanding to the western part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[267,569,1178,1204]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
. The SDM map shows an almost similar image, although the western DCR records connect Happold’s northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[729,789,1214,1240]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">DRC</collectingCountry>
area with the West African one.
</paragraph>
